: Add docker-build target for WorkloadManager\n151:   - Purpose: Add Makefile target for building workloadmanager image\n152:   - File: `Makefile`\n153:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build:\" Makefile && grep \"docker/Dockerfile\" Makefile`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T4.2**: Add docker-build-router target\n156:   - Purpose: Add Makefile target for building router image\n157:   - File: `Makefile`\n158:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build-router:\" Makefile && grep \"Dockerfile.router\" Makefile`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T4.3**: Add docker-build-picod target\n161:   - Purpose: Add Makefile target for building picod image\n162:   - File: `Makefile`\n163:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build-picod:\" Makefile && grep \"Dockerfile.picod\" Makefile`\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T4.4**: Add docker-build-all aggregate target\n166:   - Purpose: Build all three images with single target\n167:   - File: `Makefile`\n168:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-build-all:\" Makefile`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **T4.5**: Add docker-buildx-push targets for multi-arch builds\n171:   - Purpose: Support linux/amd64,linux/arm64 multi-arch builds\n172:   - File: `Makefile`\n173:   - Verification: `grep \"docker-buildx-push\" Makefile && grep \"linux/amd64,linux/arm64\" Makefile`\n174: \n175: ### Phase 5: Dockerfile Syntax Validation (ST-5)\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T5.1**: Verify all three Dockerfiles exist\n178:   - Purpose: Confirm Dockerfile files created\n179:   - File: `docker/`\n180:   - Verification: `test -f docker/Dockerfile && test -f docker/Dockerfile.router && test -f docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T5.2**: Verify workloadmanager has multi-stage structure\n183:   - Purpose: Confirm two-stage build pattern\n184:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n185:   - Verification: `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile | grep \"2\"`\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T5.3**: Verify router has multi-stage structure\n188:   - Purpose: Confirm two-stage build pattern\n189:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n190:   - Verification: `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile.router | grep \"2\"`\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T5.4**: Verify picod has multi-stage structure\n193:   - Purpose: Confirm two-stage build pattern\n194:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n195:   - Verification: `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile.picod | grep \"2\"`\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T5.5**: Verify Alpine Dockerfiles use golang:1.24-alpine builder\n198:   - Purpose: Confirm Alpine builder base for workloadmanager/router\n199:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n200:   - Verification: `grep \"golang:1.24-alpine\" docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.6**: Verify Alpine runtime Dockerfiles have USER 1000\n203:   - Purpose: Confirm non-root user for workloadmanager/router\n204:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n205:   - Verification: `grep \"USER 1000\" docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router`\n206: \n207: - [ ] **T5.7**: Verify picod runs as root (no USER directive)\n208:   - Purpose: Confirm root privileges for sandbox management\n209:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n210:   - Verification: `grep \"USER\" docker/Dockerfile.picod || echo \"OK\"`\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T5.8**: Verify all Dockerfiles have CGO_ENABLED=0\n213:   - Purpose: Confirm static compilation setting\n214:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`, `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n215:   - Verification: `grep \"CGO_ENABLED=0\" docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n216: \n217: - [ ] **T5.9**: Verify all Dockerfiles have ldflags=\"-w -s\" optimization\n218:   - Purpose: Confirm binary size optimization\n219:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`, `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n220:   - Verification: `grep \"ldflags\" docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n221: \n222: ### Phase 6: Build Execution Tests (ST-6)\n223: \n224: - [ ] **T6.1**: Build workloadmanager image successfully\n225:   - Purpose: Verify workloadmanager builds without errors\n226:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n227:   - Verification: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t agentcube-test-workloadmanager . && echo \"PASS\"`\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T6.2**: Build router image successfully\n230:   - Purpose: Verify router builds without errors\n231:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n232:   - Verification: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-test-router . && echo \"PASS\"`\n233: \n234: - [ ] **T6.3**: Build picod image successfully\n235:   - Purpose: Verify picod builds without errors\n236:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n237:   - Verification: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t agentcube-test-picod . && echo \"PASS\"`\n238: \n239: - [ ] **T6.4**: Verify workloadmanager image size <50MB\n240:   - Purpose: Confirm image meets size target\n241:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n242:   - Verification: `docker image inspect agentcube-test-workloadmanager --format='{{.Size}}' | awk '{if($1<50000000) print \"PASS\"; else print \"FAIL\"}'`\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T6.5**: Verify router image size <50MB\n245:   - Purpose: Confirm image meets size target\n246:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n247:   - Verification: `docker image inspect agentcube-test-router --format='{{.Size}}' | awk '{if($1<50000000) print \"PASS\"; else print \"FAIL\"}'`\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T6.6**: Verify picod image size <100MB\n250:   - Purpose: Confirm image meets size target (Ubuntu base larger)\n251:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n252:   - Verification: `docker image inspect agentcube-test-picod --format='{{.Size}}' | awk '{if($1<100000000) print \"PASS\"; else print \"FAIL\"}'`\n253: \n254: ### Phase 7: Runtime Verification Tests (ST-7)\n255: \n256: - [ ] **T7.1**: Verify workloadmanager binary exists in runtime image\n257:   - Purpose: Confirm binary copied from builder\n258:   - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n259:   - Verification: `docker run --rm agentcube-test-workloadmanager test -f /app/