ile: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n299:   - Verification: `docker run --rm agentcube-test-picod which python3`\n300: \n301: ### Phase 8: Makefile Integration Tests (ST-8)\n302: \n303: - [ ] **T8.1**: Run make docker-build successfully\n304:   - Purpose: Verify Makefile target works\n305:   - File: `Makefile`\n306:   - Verification: `make docker-build IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test`\n307: \n308: - [ ] **T8.2**: Run make docker-build-router successfully\n309:   - Purpose: Verify Makefile target works\n310:   - File: `Makefile`\n311:   - Verification: `make docker-build-router IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test`\n312: \n313: - [ ] **T8.3**: Run make docker-build-picod successfully\n314:   - Purpose: Verify Makefile target works\n315:   - File: `Makefile`\n316:   - Verification: `make docker-build-picod IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test`\n317: \n318: - [ ] **T8.4**: Run make docker-build-all successfully\n319:   - Purpose: Verify aggregate target builds all images\n320:   - File: `Makefile`\n321:   - Verification: `make docker-build-all IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test`\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Task Dependencies\n326: \n327: ```\n328: Phase 1 (WorkloadManager Dockerfile) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n329: T1.1 (builder FROM) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.2 (go mod download + cache)\n330:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.3 (COPY source + CGO_ENABLED)\n331:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.4 (go build + ldflags)\n332:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.5 (runtime FROM alpine)\n333:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.6 (apk packages)\n334:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.7 (adduser apiserver)\n335:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.8 (COPY --from=builder)\n336:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.9 (USER + EXPOSE)\n337:                       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ T1.10 (ENTRYPOINT)\n338: \n339: Phase 2 (Router Dockerfile) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n340: T2.1 (builder FROM) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.2 (go mod download + cache)\n341:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.3 (COPY client-go/)\n342:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.4 (CGO + go build)\n343:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.5 (runtime FROM alpine)\n344:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.6 (apk + adduser router)\n345:                       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.7 (COPY --from=builder + USER)\n346:                       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ T2.8 (EXPOSE + ENTRYPOINT)\n347: \n348: Phase 3 (PicoD Dockerfile) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n349: T3.1 (builder FROM golang) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T3.2 (go mod download)\n350:                              ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T3.3 (CGO + go build)\n351:                              ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T3.4 (runtime FROM ubuntu)\n352:                              ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T3.5 (apt-get python3)\n353:                              ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T3.6 (COPY --from=builder)\n354:                              ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ T3.7 (EXPOSE + ENTRYPOINT)\n355: \n356: Phase 4 (Makefile Targets) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n357: T1.1-T1.10 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T4.1 (docker-build)\n358: T2.1-T2.8 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T4.2 (docker-build-router)\n359: T3.1-T3.7 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T4.3 (docker-build-picod)\n360:              ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T4.4 (docker-build-all)\n361:              ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ T4.5 (docker-buildx-push)\n362: \n363: Phase 5 (Syntax Validation) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n364: T1.1-T4.5 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T5.1-T5.9 (syntax checks)\n365: \n366: Phase 6 (Build Execution) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n367: T5.1-T5.9 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T6.1-T6.3 (build tests)\n368:             ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T6.4-T6.6 (size verification)\n369: \n370: Phase 7 (Runtime Verification) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n371: T6.1-T6.6 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T7.1-T7.9 (runtime tests)\n372: \n373: Phase 8 (Makefile Integration) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\n374: T4.1-T4.5 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T8.1-T8.4 (make target tests)\n375: ```\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Verification Commands\n380: \n381: | Task Phase | Verification Command |\n382: |------------|----------------------|\n383: | Phase 1 | `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile | grep \"2\"` |\n384: | Phase 2 | `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile.router | grep \"2\"` |\n385: | Phase 3 | `grep -c \"FROM\" docker/Dockerfile.picod | grep \"2\"` |\n386: | Phase 4 | `grep \"docker-build-all:\" Makefile` |\n387: | Phase 5 | `grep \"CGO_ENABLED=0\" docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router docker/Dockerfile.picod` |\n388: | Phase 6 | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t test-workloadmanager . && docker image inspect test-workloadmanager --format='{{.Size}}'` |\n389: | Phase 7 | `docker run --rm test-workloadmanager id -u | grep \"1000\"` |\n390: | Phase 8 | `make docker-build-all IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test` |\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ## Acceptance Criteria\n395: \n396: - [ ] WorkloadManager Dockerfile has 2-stage build structure\n397: - [ ] Router Dockerfile has 2-stage build structure\n398: - [ ] PicoD Dockerfile has 2-stage build structure\n399: - [ ] WorkloadManager uses golang:1.24-alpine builder + alpine:3.19 runtime\n400: - [ ] Router uses golang:1.24-alpine builder + alpine:3.19 runtime\n401: - [ ] PicoD uses golang:1.24 builder + ubuntu:24.04 runtime\n402: - [ ] WorkloadManager runs as UID 1000 (non-root)\n403: - [ ] Router runs as UID 1000 (non-root)\n404: - [ ] PicoD runs as root (UID 0)\n405: - [ ] All Dockerfiles have CGO_ENABLED=0\n406: - [ ] All Dockerfiles have ldflags=\"-w -s\" optimization\n407: - [ ] WorkloadManager/Router use BuildKit cache mounts for go mod/go build\n408: - [ ] Router Dockerfile includes client-go/ COPY\n409: - [ ] PicoD Dockerfile installs python3, python3-pip\n410: - [ ] WorkloadManager image size <50MB\n411: - [ ] Router image size <50MB\n412: - [ ] PicoD image size <100MB\n413: - [ ] Makefile has docker-build target\n414: - [ ] Makefile has docker-build-router target\n415: - [ ] Makefile has docker-build-picod target\n416: - [ ] Makefile has docker-build-all target\n417: - [ ] Makefile has docker-buildx-push targets for multi-arch\n418: - [ ] Runtime images have no Go toolchain\n419: - [ ] Runtime images have no Go source files\n420: - [ ] All images build successfully with make docker-build-all\n421: \n422: ---\n423: \n424: ## File Changes Summary\n425: \n426: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n427: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n428: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Create | 25 | WorkloadManager multi-stage build (builder ‚Üí runtime) |\n429: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Create | 30 | Router multi-stage build (builder ‚Üí runtime with client-go) |\n430: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Create | 25 | PicoD multi-stage build (builder ‚Üí Ubuntu runtime) |\n431: | `Makefile` | Modify | 35 | Add docker-build, docker-build-router, docker-build-picod, docker-build-all, docker-buildx-push targets |\n432: \n433: ---\n434: \n435: ## Implementation Notes\n436: \n437: ### Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n438: \n439: ```dockerfile\n440: # Stage 1: Builder\n441: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n442: WORKDIR /app\n443: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n444: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod go mod download\n445: COPY . .\n446: ENV CGO_ENABLED=0\n447: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n448:     go build -ldflags=\"-w -s\" -o /app/bin/<binary> ./cmd/<module>\n449: \n450: # Stage 2: Runtime\n451: FROM alpine:3.19\n452: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates tzdata\n453: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 <user>\n454: WORKDIR /app\n455: COPY --from=builder /app/bin/<binary> /app/bin/<binary>\n456: USER 1000\n457: EXPOSE 8080\n458: ENTRYPOINT [\" /app/bin/<binary>\"]\n459: ```\n460: \n461: ### BuildKit Cache Optimization\n462: \n463: | Cache Mount | Target | Purpose |\n464: |-------------|--------|---------|\n465: | `/go/pkg/mod` | Module cache | Persist module downloads across builds |\n466: | `/root/.cache/go-build` | Build cache | Cache compiled artifacts |\n467: \n468: ### Binary Size Optimization Flags\n469: \n470: | Flag | Effect |\n471: |------|--------|\n472: | `-w` | Strip DWARF debug information |\n473: | `-s` | Strip symbol table |\n474: | `CGO_ENABLED=0` | Static-like compilation |\n475: \n476: ### User Security Context\n477: \n478: | Image | User | Reason |\n479: |-------|------|--------|\n480: | WorkloadManager | UID 1000 | Non-root for security |\n481: | Router | UID 1000 | Non-root for security |\n482: | PicoD | root (UID 0) | Sandbox pod management requires elevated privileges |\n483: \n484: ---\n485: \n486: ## Implementation Timeline\n487: \n488: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n489: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n490: | Phase 1: WorkloadManager Dockerfile | T1.1-T1.10 | Pending | 0% |\n491: | Phase 2: Router Dockerfile | T2.1-T2.8 | Pending | 0% |\n492: | Phase 3: PicoD Dockerfile | T3.1-T3.7 | Pending | 0% |\n493: | Phase 4: Makefile Targets | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n494: | Phase 5: Syntax Validation | T5.1-T5.9 | Pending | 0% |\n495: | Phase 6: Build Execution | T6.1-T6.6 | Pending | 0% |\n496: | Phase 7: Runtime Verification | T7.1-T7.9 | Pending | 0% |\n497: | Phase 8: Makefile Integration | T8.1-T8.4 | Pending | 0% |\n498: \n499: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/46 tasks)**\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ## References\n504: \n505: - Design: `changes/AR-032/design.md`\n506: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n507: - Proposal: `changes/AR-032/proposal.md`\n508: - Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n509: - BuildKit cache mounts: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/#cache-mounts\n510: - Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n\n(End of file - total 510 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 ‚Äî Dockerfile Â§öÈò∂ÊÆµÊûÑÂª∫ Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-032 ‚Äî Dockerfile Â§öÈò∂ÊÆµÊûÑÂª∫ (3 images) |\n| Module | `docker` |\n| Language | Dockerfile |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: WorkloadManager Dockerfile Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create builder stage with golang:1.24-alpine base\n  - Purpose: Define builder stage for Go compilation","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775886798154,"end":1775886798174}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886798179,"sessionID":"ses_284e6d739ffeDjSqpTZfzDdTLA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1a0be6001EbjxIuosncFYCf","messageID":"msg_d7b19a031001EsM059y3sCKIT4","sessionID":"ses_284e6d739ffeDjSqpTZfzDdTLA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-620f7be15aa74a26ae1d8d04c8ffc691","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 ‚Äî Dockerfile Â§öÈò∂ÊÆµÊûÑÂª∫ (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Ê¶ÇËø∞\n4: \n5: | Â±ûÊÄß | ÂÄº |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-032 |\n8: | Module | docker |\n9: | Language | Dockerfile |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (ÁõÆÁöÑ)\n15: \n16: Define multi-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for:\n17: \n18: 1. **Build Separation**: Isolate Go compilation (builder stage) from runtime environment to reduce final image size\n19: 2. **Security**: Run containers as non-root users with minimal runtime dependencies\n20: 3. **Build Efficiency**: Leverage BuildKit cache mounts for Go module downloads to accelerate CI builds\n21: 4. **Consistency**: Standardize Dockerfile structure across workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n22: \n23: **Target Images**:\n24: \n25: | Image | Binary | Runtime Base | User |\n26: |-------|--------|--------------|------|\n27: | `workloadmanager` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `alpine:3.19` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n28: | `agentcube-router` | `./cmd/router` | `alpine:3.19` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n29: | `picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `ubuntu:24.04` | `root` (sandbox permissions) |\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. Scope (ËåÉÂõ¥)\n34: \n35: ### 2.1 In Scope\n36: \n37: | Deliverable | Description |\n38: |-------------|-------------|\n39: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Multi-stage build for Workload Manager (builder ‚Üí runtime) |\n40: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for Router (builder ‚Üí runtime) |\n41: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Multi-stage build for PicoD (builder ‚Üí runtime) |\n42: | `Makefile docker-* targets` | Build targets referencing Dockerfiles (already exist) |\n43: | Build args documentation | `TARGETOS`, `TARGETARCH` platform args for cross-compilation |\n44: \n45: ### 2.2 Dockerfile Stage Structure\n46: \n47: **Workload Manager / Router (2-stage)**:\n48: \n49: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n50: |-------|------|---------|\n51: | `builder` | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | Go compilation with BuildKit cache mounts |\n52: | `runtime` | `alpine:3.19` | Minimal runtime with ca-certificates, non-root user |\n53: \n54: **PicoD (2-stage)**:\n55: \n56: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n57: |-------|------|---------|\n58: | `builder` | `golang:1.24.4` | Go compilation |\n59: | `runtime` | `ubuntu:24.04` | Python3 dependency for sandbox execution, runs as root |\n60: \n61: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n62: \n63: | Item | Reason |\n64: |------|--------|\n65: | Multi-arch buildx configuration | Covered by existing `docker-buildx-*` Make targets |\n66: | Docker registry push logic | Covered by `docker-buildx-push-*` targets and CI workflow |\n67: | Helm chart image references | Chart values already reference correct image names |\n68: | Volcano scheduler image | Separate component with external image repository |\n69: | Distroless base images | Alpine/Ubuntu provide sufficient minimal runtime; distroless migration is separate AR |\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 3. Impact Analysis (ÂΩ±ÂìçÂàÜÊûê)\n74: \n75: ### 3.1 Êñ∞Â¢ûÊñá‰ª∂\n76: \n77: | File | Description |\n78: |------|-------------|\n79: | N/A | Dockerfiles already exist in `docker/` directory |\n80: \n81: ### 3.2 ‰øÆÊîπÊñá‰ª∂\n82: \n83: | File | Change |\n84: |------|--------|\n85: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Validate existing multi-stage pattern; add BuildKit cache mount optimization |\n86: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Add `COPY client-go/ client-go/` for Go module dependencies; validate cache mounts |\n87: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Validate builder ‚Üí runtime stage separation; document root user requirement |\n88: | `Makefile` | Ensure `docker-build-*` targets pass correct build args (`TARGETOS`, `TARGETARCH`) |\n89: \n90: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n91: \n92: | Dependency | Purpose |\n93: |------------|---------|\n94: | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | Builder stage base image for Go compilation |\n95: | `golang:1.24.4` | Builder stage base for picod (matches Go version in CI) |\n96: | `alpine:3.19` | Minimal runtime base for workloadmanager/router |\n97: | `ubuntu:24.04` | Runtime base for picod (requires Python3 for sandbox) |\n98: | `ca-certificates` | TLS certificate bundle for HTTPS connections |\n99: \n100: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n101: \n102: | Consumer | Usage |\n103: |----------|-------|\n104: | `CI: main.yml` | `make docker-build` builds workloadmanager image |\n105: | `CI: build-push-release.yml` | `make docker-buildx-push-*` pushes multi-arch images to ghcr.io |\n106: | `E2E: run_e2e.sh` | `make docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` for Kind cluster |\n107: | `Helm chart` | References images by `repository:tag` from values.yaml |\n108: | `Kind cluster` | `kind load docker-image` loads local images for E2E testing |\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (Â§áÈÄâÊñπÊ°à)\n113: \n114: ### Alternative 1: Single-stage Dockerfile (no builder separation)\n115: \n116: **Approach**: Build Go binary directly in runtime base image.\n117: \n118: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n119: |--------|------------|\n120: | Pros | Simpler Dockerfile; fewer stages |\n121: | Cons | Final image includes Go toolchain (~300MB); larger attack surface; slower image pulls |\n122: \n123: **Decision**: Rejected. Multi-stage builds produce minimal runtime images (~20MB for Alpine-based) by excluding compiler and build dependencies.\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 2: Distroless base images (gcr.io/distroless/static)\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Use distroless/static or distroless/base for runtime stage.\n128: \n129: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n130: |--------|------------|\n131: | Pros | Smallest possible image; no shell/package manager; enhanced security |\n132: | Cons | Debugging harder (no shell); requires separate debug image for troubleshooting; picod needs Python3 (distroless/static insufficient) |\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Rejected for current scope. Alpine provides minimal footprint with shell for debugging. Distroless migration should be separate AR with debug image strategy.\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 3: Shared builder stage via Dockerfile inheritance\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Create base builder Dockerfile and `FROM` it in component Dockerfiles.\n139: \n140: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n141: |--------|------------|\n142: | Pros | Reduced duplication; centralized Go version management |\n143: | Cons | Dockerfile inheritance limited; BuildKit cache mounts require explicit declaration; additional base image build step |\n144: \n145: **Decision**: Rejected. Each Dockerfile should be self-contained for CI simplicity. Go version consistency managed via Makefile variables and CI workflow Go version pins.\n146: \n147: ### Alternative 4: Static binary compilation with musl libc\n148: \n149: **Approach**: Compile with `-tags netgo,osusergo` for fully static binaries, use scratch base image.\n150: \n151: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n152: |--------|------------|\n153: | Pros | Zero-dependency runtime; smallest image size; no libc version issues |\n154: | Cons | DNS resolution requires netgo tag; Go modules with CGO disabled; picod requires Python3 dependency |\n155: \n156: **Decision**: Partially adopted. `CGO_ENABLED=0` already used; Alpine (musl libc) provides static-like behavior without scratch complexity. Fully static binaries with scratch reserved for future optimization.\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 5: Pre-built binary COPY (no in-container compilation)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Build binaries outside Docker, COPY into runtime stage.\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n163: |--------|------------|\n164: | Pros | Faster builds if binaries cached; no Go image dependency |\n165: | Cons | Requires host Go toolchain matching target platform; CI complexity for cross-arch builds; reproducibility harder to guarantee |\n166: \n167: **Decision**: Rejected. In-container compilation ensures consistent build environment, handles cross-platform compilation via `TARGETOS/TARGETARCH`, and leverages BuildKit layer caching.\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 5. Risks\n172: \n173: | Risk | Mitigation |\n174: |------|------------|\n175: | Go version drift (builder vs CI) | CI workflow pins Go 1.24.4/1.24.9; Makefile docker targets align with Dockerfile base images |\n176: | Alpine libc DNS issues | Use `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static-like compilation; ca-certificates installed for TLS |\n177: | PicoD root user security | Documented requirement for sandbox permissions; sandbox pods isolate picod from host |\n178: | BuildKit cache invalidation | `go mod download` cache mount keyed by `go.mod/go.sum` hash; CI uses Buildx with cache export |\n179: | Image size bloat | Multi-stage ensures only binary copied to runtime; Alpine base ~5MB overhead |\n180: | Cross-arch build failures | Makefile `docker-buildx` targets use `--platform linux/amd64,arm64` with `TARGETOS/TARGETARCH` args |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n185: \n186: - [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile` multi-stage structure (builder ‚Üí runtime)\n187: - [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile.router` includes `COPY client-go/ client-go/`\n188: - [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile.picod` uses `ubuntu:24.04` runtime with Python3\n189: - [ ] Verify BuildKit cache mounts: `--mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod`\n190: - [ ] Verify `CGO_ENABLED=0` in build command\n191: - [ ] Verify non-root user in workloadmanager/router runtime stages\n192: - [ ] Test `make docker-build` produces <50MB runtime image\n193: - [ ] Test `make docker-build-router` produces <50MB runtime image\n194: - [ ] Test `make docker-build-picod` produces functional image\n195: - [ ] Verify `TARGETOS=linux TARGETARCH=amd64` produces correct binary\n196: - [ ] Verify `TARGETOS=linux TARGETARCH=arm64` cross-compilation works\n197: - [ ] E2E test: `kind load docker-image` succeeds for all 3 images\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## 7. References\n202: \n203: - Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n204: - BuildKit cache mounts: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/#cache-mounts\n205: - Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n206: - deployment/design.md ‚Äî Dockerfiles section (lines 157-178)\n207: - ci-cd/design.md ‚Äî Build targets and CI workflow (lines 173-179)\n208: - deployment/spec.md ‚Äî Docker images requirement (line 77-83)\n209: - manifests/charts/base/values.yaml ‚Äî Image repository/tag defaults\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 ‚Äî Dockerfile Â§öÈò∂ÊÆµÊûÑÂª∫ (3 images)\n\n## Ê¶ÇËø∞\n\n| Â±ûÊÄß | ÂÄº |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-032 |\n| Module | docker |\n| Language | Dockerfile |\n| Size | S |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (ÁõÆÁöÑ)\n\nDefine multi-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for:\n\n1. **Build Separation**: Isolate Go compilation (builder stage) from runtime environment to reduce final image size\n2. **Security**: Run containers as non-root users with minimal runtime dependencies\n3. **Build Efficiency**: Leverage BuildKit cache mounts for Go module downloads to accelerate CI builds","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886798157,"end":1775886798177}}}}
